page_id: S4-LNX-02
title: AreaMatrix Library
description: Browse the connected Linux repository through C4-11 desktop-main-query.
toolbar:
  - Import
  - Search
  - Refresh
  - Settings
navigation:
  - All Files
  - Recent
  - Needs Review
  - Categories from list_tree_json
sync_conflict_entry:
  page_id: S4-X-03
  banner: Sync conflict needs review
  list: Needs Review
  detail_banner: This file has a sync conflict
  source: SyncConflictEntryViewModel
replace_confirm:
  page_id: S4-X-09
  source: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.OpenReviewRouteAsync
  core_preview: preview_sync_conflict_resolution
  core_apply: resolve_sync_conflict
file_list:
  columns:
    - Name
    - Category
    - Modified
    - Size
    - Status
detail:
  empty: Repository summary and import entry
  tabs:
    - Meta
    - Log
    - Note
status_bar:
  - Local folder
  - Watcher: platform status
  - DB: ready
states:
  loading: Loading repository...
  refreshing: Refreshing...
  db_locked: Keep cached list and show retry
  permission_denied: Show readable error without chmod
  missing_file: Show missing status and recovery entry
actions:
  open_repository: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.OpenRepositoryAsync
  refresh: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.RefreshAsync
  refresh_conflicts: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.RefreshAsync
  search: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.RunSearchAsync
  load_more: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.LoadMoreAsync
  select_category: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.SelectCategoryAsync
  select_file: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.SelectFileAsync
pagination:
  page_size: 50
  state: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.PaginationText
  next_page_enabled: LinuxMainWindowViewModel.CanLoadMore
safety:
  - The page calls list_files through DesktopMainQueryCoreBridge.
  - The page calls get_file through DesktopMainQueryCoreBridge.
  - The page calls list_tree_json through DesktopMainQueryCoreBridge.
  - The page calls search_files through DesktopMainQueryCoreBridge.
  - The page calls detect_sync_conflicts through SyncConflictEntryCoreBridge for S4-X-03.
  - The S4-X-09 route calls preview_sync_conflict_resolution before enabling Replace.
  - Replace requires a Core preview token, Replace plan, Trash/Core backup evidence, and second confirmation.
  - Confirmed Replace calls resolve_sync_conflict; the Linux UI never directly overwrites files.
  - Load more advances FileFilter/SearchPagination offset through DesktopMainQueryCoreBridge.
  - Refresh only reloads the current snapshot and never runs reindex or rescan.
  - The Linux UI does not scan the repository filesystem to build the list.
  - The sync conflict entry does not implement watcher health, import commit, rescan confirm, or recovery.
